  {
    "id": "session-10-it-s-a-long-ass-way_title",
    "type": "header",
    "props": {
      "title": "Session 10 - It's a Long Ass Way!",
      "color": "gold",
      "size": "md",
      "col": "1",
      "row": "6",
      "colSpan": "1",
      "rowSpan": "1"
    }
  },
  {
    "id": "session-10-it-s-a-long-ass-way_summary",
    "type": "text",
    "props": {
      "content": "The kNight Watch rode out from Scarwatch Hold toward the eastern crags to investigate the Radiant Eye cult outpost and secure a lost celestial instrument while pursuing Isgo's kidnappers. They discovered Isgo's horse Bullseye and learned that two unknown riders had taken him, then endured several days of difficult travel through increasingly craggy terrain. Along the way they found a hidden cache of gold and potions, discovered a decomposed corpse, and defeated a Xorn that erupted from the earth. The session ended as Meles scouted ahead and spotted two figures in tan robes, who attacked the party as they approached.",
      "col": "1",
      "row": "7",
      "colSpan": "1",
      "rowSpan": "1"
    }
  },
  {
    "id": "session-10-it-s-a-long-ass-way_recording_1",
    "type": "media-player",
    "props": {
      "title": "Session 10 Recording",
      "src": "https://drive.google.com/file/d/1Wqf4bV8GRHBkJAmu8d7PEVSoudjcuyYH/view?usp=sharing",
      "mediaType": "auto",
      "caption": "",
      "col": "1",
      "row": "8",
      "colSpan": "1",
      "rowSpan": "2",
      "displayMode": "image-button",
      "image": "/images/dragon-ears.png"
    }
  },
  {
    "id": "session-9-a-cart-time-job_title",
    "type": "header",
    "props": {
      "title": "Session 9 - A Cart-time Job",
      "color": "gold",
      "size": "md",
      "col": "1",
      "row": "10",
      "colSpan": "1",
      "rowSpan": "1"
    }
  },
  {
    "id": "session-9-a-cart-time-job_summary",
    "type": "text",
    "props": {
      "content": "In Scarwatch Hold, the kNight Watch received their assignment from Warden Haliun to hunt Isgo. Umlin commissioned the party to complete a map of the eastern lands for 20 gold pieces. Shopping and tavern time followed, including reunions with Dempsey and Meles. The next morning the Radiant Eye cult symbol appeared on the Sanctuary wall, shifting priorities. Nambra redirected them to investigate the cult outpost in the eastern crags and secure a lost celestial instrument from nearby ruins. The party rode out mid-morning toward the crags, crossing the drawbridge as a lone black horse with a white blaze appeared riderless in the distance.",
      "col": "1",
      "row": "11",
      "colSpan": "1",
      "rowSpan": "1"
    }
  },
  {
    "id": "session-9-a-cart-time-job_recording_1",
    "type": "media-player",
    "props": {
      "title": "Session 09 Recording",
      "src": "https://drive.google.com/file/d/1CjvCopdzZqfofggQBuYuZh_1RANjyCjA/view?usp=sharing",
      "mediaType": "auto",
      "caption": "",
      "col": "1",
      "row": "12",
      "colSpan": "1",
      "rowSpan": "2",
      "displayMode": "image-button",
      "image": "/images/dragon-ears.png"
    }
  },
  {
    "id": "session-8-mimic-at-the-gate_title",
    "type": "header",
    "props": {
      "title": "Session 8 - Mimic at the Gate",
      "color": "gold",
      "size": "md",
      "col": "1",
      "row": "14",
      "colSpan": "1",
      "rowSpan": "1"
    }
  },
  {
    "id": "session-8-mimic-at-the-gate_summary",
    "type": "text",
    "props": {
      "content": "In Scarwatch Hold, the party was wrapping up local personal matters and responsibilities around the K9 Crew prisoners. A smoking wagon arrived and a mimic disguised as a barrel attacked with acidic tendrils. The adventurers fought it off fiercely. Nixie and Aeon delivered the prisoners' charges to Warden Naevaris Haliun, who confirmed the judgment for the next day. That night a shadowy burglar was driven from the bank. The following morning the Cap'n confessed dealings with the Scorpion as Draelith messed with the sending stone. A mysterious voice replied that their interference had complicated matters yet perhaps the party would be useful.",
      "col": "1",
      "row": "15",
      "colSpan": "1",
      "rowSpan": "1"
    }
  },
  {
    "id": "session-8-mimic-at-the-gate_recording_1",
    "type": "media-player",
    "props": {
      "title": "Session 08 Recording",
      "src": "https://drive.google.com/file/d/1uFpAxFkMTSZBX6WJOVRt2z1yf-zV3316/view?usp=sharing",
      "mediaType": "auto",
      "caption": "",
      "col": "1",
      "row": "16",
      "colSpan": "1",
      "rowSpan": "2",
      "displayMode": "image-button",
      "image": "/images/dragon-ears.png"
    }
  },
  {
    "id": "session-7-brooch-the-subject_title",
    "type": "header",
    "props": {
      "title": "Session 7 - Brooch the Subject",
      "color": "gold",
      "size": "md",
      "col": "1",
      "row": "18",
      "colSpan": "1",
      "rowSpan": "1"
    }
  },
  {
    "id": "session-7-brooch-the-subject_summary",
    "type": "text",
    "props": {
      "content": "The party's primary goal was to escort the captured K9 Crew bandits, including their wounded leader Captain Kinrik, from Hesfal to Scarwatch Hold and personally deliver them along with the sealed charges directly to Warden Haliun in the citadel. On the road, they encountered the abrasive half-orc Isgo, who recognized the crew; after some taunting from Draelith and intimidation by Nova, he backed off, though Meles later confirmed the Blackshield family smiths had clashed with him earlier and emerged unharmed. The group reached Scarwatch Hold without major incident, secured lodging, gathered rumors at the tavern, and the next morning pressed forward to complete the handover, only for a massive explosion to erupt at the Outer Gates, ending the session on that sudden, chaotic note.",
      "col": "1",
      "row": "19",
      "colSpan": "1",
      "rowSpan": "1"
    }
  },
  {
    "id": "session-7-brooch-the-subject_recording_1",
    "type": "media-player",
    "props": {
      "title": "Session 07 Recording",
      "src": "https://drive.google.com/file/d/1PaRnBFJq64OK1WQ4Cqj54iyPxdb1Rzte/view?usp=sharing",
      "mediaType": "auto",
      "caption": "",
      "col": "1",
      "row": "20",
      "colSpan": "1",
      "rowSpan": "2",
      "displayMode": "image-button",
      "image": "/images/dragon-ears.png"
    }
  },
  {
    "id": "session-6-rope-a-dope_title",
    "type": "header",
    "props": {
      "title": "Session 6 - Rope A Dope",
      "color": "gold",
      "size": "md",
      "col": "1",
      "row": "22",
      "colSpan": "1",
      "rowSpan": "1"
    }
  },
  {
    "id": "session-6-rope-a-dope_summary",
    "type": "text",
    "props": {
      "content": "The party focused on securing their prisoners and uncovering the true scope of the plot behind the chaos in Hesfal. They learned that the bandits were being directed through an amplified sending stone embedded in a magically attuned cavern, confirming that the Scorpion had planned more than a simple robbery and jailbreak. While investigating the depths of the hideout, the party fought and defeated dangerous creatures drawn to the cavern's magic, revealing a potential path toward the Underdark below. After returning the bandits to Hesfal and agreeing to transport them to Scarwatch Hold, the session ended with a final shock as an unknown figure was discovered rifling through Nova's belongings, signaling that the danger was far from over.",
      "col": "1",
      "row": "23",
      "colSpan": "1",
      "rowSpan": "1"
    }
  },
  {
    "id": "session-6-rope-a-dope_recording_1",
    "type": "media-player",
    "props": {
      "title": "Session 06 Recording",
      "src": "https://drive.google.com/file/d/1dH5n001GD34dgZV9sflUoUiSoug_pcAA/view?usp=sharing",
      "mediaType": "auto",
      "caption": "",
      "col": "1",
      "row": "24",
      "colSpan": "1",
      "rowSpan": "2",
      "displayMode": "image-button",
      "image": "/images/dragon-ears.png"
    }
  },
  {
    "id": "session-5-the-hots-for-nova_title",
    "type": "header",
    "props": {
      "title": "Session 5 - The Hots for Nova",
      "color": "gold",
      "size": "md",
      "col": "1",
      "row": "26",
      "colSpan": "1",
      "rowSpan": "1"
    }
  },
  {
    "id": "session-5-the-hots-for-nova_summary",
    "type": "text",
    "props": {
      "content": "An ambush was set up to catch the escaped bandits and uncover who had orchestrated the chaos in Hesfal. Their ambush indirectly paid off, leading them from the bandits' horse drop through dangerous terrain to a hidden cave where they decisively dismantled the crew and forced their surrender. Interrogation revealed that the robbery, jailbreak, and murder arrest were all part of a paid plan meant to spread fear during Salvus, ordered by an unknown figure called the Scorpion. Everything came to an end with the chilling realization that their unseen employer was still watching, as a disembodied voice questioned the failure of the plan.",
      "col": "1",
      "row": "27",
      "colSpan": "1",
      "rowSpan": "1"
    }
  },
  {
    "id": "session-5-the-hots-for-nova_recording_1",
    "type": "media-player",
    "props": {
      "title": "Session 05 Recording",
      "src": "https://drive.google.com/file/d/1PYKRdgQ71fcUERMgsEx57vXWpcCdeIwM/view?usp=sharing",
